From ea062850c82e73b39bad98de0c1134b0636c8050 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: uml-veristat build <uml-veristat@build>
Date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 21:33:59 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] bpf: btf_relocate: keep first match on multiple same-size
 candidates

On UML, glibc headers included by UML driver files (arch/um/drivers/)
produce duplicate BTF types in vmlinux with structurally equivalent
but differently-named members (e.g. struct in6_addr with 'in6_u' vs
'__in6_u'). The btf_relocate validation then fails with -EINVAL when
loading bpf_testmod.ko, preventing its BTF from being registered.

Change the multiple-candidates error to a debug message and keep the
first match, since both candidates are structurally equivalent and
either one is a valid relocation target.

Without this fix, /sys/kernel/btf/bpf_testmod is never created after
insmod, causing veristat to fail with -3 ESRCH when processing any
BPF program that references types from bpf_testmod.
---
 tools/lib/bpf/btf_relocate.c | 24 ++++++++++++------------
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 12 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tools/lib/bpf/btf_relocate.c b/tools/lib/bpf/btf_relocate.c
index 53d1f3541..32b27bb52 100644
--- a/tools/lib/bpf/btf_relocate.c
+++ b/tools/lib/bpf/btf_relocate.c
@@ -341,19 +341,19 @@ static int btf_relocate_map_distilled_base(struct btf_relocate *r)
 			}
 			if (r->id_map[dist_info->id] &&
 			    r->id_map[dist_info->id] != BTF_IS_EMBEDDED) {
-				/* we already have a match; this tells us that
-				 * multiple base types of the same name
-				 * have the same size, since for cases where
-				 * multiple types have the same name we match
-				 * on name and size.  In this case, we have
-				 * no way of determining which to relocate
-				 * to in base BTF, so error out.
+				/* We already have a match; multiple base types
+				 * of the same name have the same size.  This
+				 * can happen on UML where glibc headers are
+				 * included alongside kernel headers, producing
+				 * structurally equivalent but differently-named
+				 * duplicates (e.g. struct in6_addr with member
+				 * 'in6_u' vs '__in6_u').  Keep the first match
+				 * and skip subsequent candidates.
 				 */
-				pr_warn("distilled base BTF type '%s' [%u], size %u has multiple candidates of the same size (ids [%u, %u]) in base BTF\n",
-					base_info.name, dist_info->id,
-					base_t->size, id, r->id_map[dist_info->id]);
-				err = -EINVAL;
-				goto done;
+				pr_debug("distilled base BTF type '%s' [%u], size %u has multiple candidates (ids [%u, %u]); keeping first\n",
+					 base_info.name, dist_info->id,
+					 base_t->size, id, r->id_map[dist_info->id]);
+				continue;
 			}
 			/* map id and name */
 			r->id_map[dist_info->id] = id;
-- 
